Field.Name: Account
Field.Description: Account mnemonic as agreed between broker and institution.

Field.Name: AdvId
Field.Description: Unique identifier of advertisement message. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: AdvRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE transaction types. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: AdvSide
Field.Description: Broker's side of advertised trade

Field.Name: AdvTransType
Field.Description: Identifies advertisement message transaction type

Field.Name: AvgPx
Field.Description: Calculated average price of all fills on this order.

Field.Name: BeginSeqNo
Field.Description: Message sequence number of first message in range to be resent

Field.Name: BeginString
Field.Description: Identifies beginning of new message and protocol version. ALWAYS FIRST FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted)

Field.Name: BodyLength
Field.Description: Message length, in bytes, forward to the CheckSum field. ALWAYS SECOND FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted)

Field.Name: CheckSum
Field.Description: Three byte, simple checksum (see Appendix B: CheckSum Calculation for description). ALWAYS LAST FIELD IN MESSAGE; i.e. serves, with the trailing <SOH>, as the end-of-message delimiter. Always defined as three characters. (Always unencrypted)

Field.Name: ClOrdID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by institution (identified by SenderCompID or OnBehalfOfCompID as appropriate). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms, particularly those which electronically submit multi-day orders, trade globally or throughout market close periods,should ensure uniqueness across days, for example by embedding a date within the ClOrdID field.

Field.Name: Commission
Field.Description: Commission. Note if CommType is percentage, Commission of 5% should be represented as .05.

Field.Name: CommType
Field.Description: Commission type

Field.Name: CumQty
Field.Description: Total number of shares filled. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: Currency
Field.Description: Identifies currency used for price. Absence of this field is interpreted as the default for the security. It is recommended that systems provide the currency value whenever possible. See Appendix A: Valid Currency Codes for information on obtaining valid values.

Field.Name: EndSeqNo
Field.Description: Message sequence number of last message in range to be resent. If request is for a single message BeginSeqNo = EndSeqNo. If request is for all messages subsequent to a particular message, EndSeqNo = "0" (representing infinity).

Field.Name: ExecID
Field.Description: Unique identifier of execution message as assigned by broker (will be 0 (zero) for ExecTransType=3 (Status)). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day or the life of a multi-day order. Firms which accept multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the ExecID field to assure uniqueness across days. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: ExecInst
Field.Description: Instructions for order handling on exchange trading floor. If more than one instruction is applicable to an order, this field can contain multiple instructions separated by space.

Field.Name: ExecRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier used with Cancel and Correct transaction types. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: ExecTransType
Field.Description: Identifies transaction type

Field.Name: HandlInst
Field.Description: Instructions for order handling on Broker trading floor

Field.Name: IDSource
Field.Description: Identifies class of alternative SecurityID

Field.Name: IOIid
Field.Description: Unique identifier of IOI message. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: IOIQltyInd
Field.Description: Relative quality of indication

Field.Name: IOIRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE, transaction types. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: IOIShares
Field.Description: Number of shares in numeric or relative size.

Field.Name: IOITransType
Field.Description: Identifies IOI message transaction type

Field.Name: LastCapacity
Field.Description: Broker capacity in order execution

Field.Name: LastMkt
Field.Description: Market of execution for last fill

Field.Name: LastPx
Field.Description: Price of this (last) fill. Field not required for ExecTransType = 3 (Status)

Field.Name: LastShares
Field.Description: Quantity of shares bought/sold on this (last) fill. Field not required for ExecTransType = 3 (Status) (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: LinesOfText
Field.Description: Identifies number of lines of text body

Field.Name: MsgSeqNum
Field.Description: Integer message sequence number.

Field.Name: MsgType
Field.Description: Defines message type. ALWAYS THIRD FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted) Note: A "U" as the first character in the MsgType field (i.e. U1, U2, etc) indicates that the message format is privately defined between the sender and receiver.

Field.Name: NewSeqNo
Field.Description: New sequence number

Field.Name: OrderID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by broker. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which accept multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the OrderID field to assure uniqueness across days.

Field.Name: OrderQty
Field.Description: Number of shares ordered. This represents the number of shares for equities or based on normal convention the number of contracts for options, futures, convertible bonds, etc. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: OrdStatus
Field.Description: Identifies current status of order.

Field.Name: OrdType
Field.Description: Order type.

Field.Name: OrigClOrdID
Field.Description: ClOrdID of the previous order (NOT the initial order of the day) as assigned by the institution, used to identify the previous order in cancel and cancel/replace requests.

Field.Name: OrigTime
Field.Description: Time of message origination (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT"))

Field.Name: PossDupFlag
Field.Description: Indicates possible retransmission of message with this sequence number

Field.Name: Price
Field.Description: Price per share

Field.Name: RefSeqNum
Field.Description: Reference message sequence number

Field.Name: RelatdSym
Field.Description: Symbol of issue related to story. Can be repeated within message to identify multiple companies.

Field.Name: Rule80A
Field.Description: Note that the name of this field is changing to "OrderCapacity" as Rule80A is a very US market-specific term. Other world markets need to convey similar information, however, often a subset of the US values. . See the "Rule80A (aka OrderCapacity) Usage by Market" appendix for market-specific usage of this field.

Field.Name: SecurityID
Field.Description: CUSIP or other alternate security identifier

Field.Name: SenderCompID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify firm sending message.

Field.Name: SenderSubID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (desk, trader, etc.)

Field.Name: SendingDate
Field.Description: No longer used. Included here for reference to prior versions.

Field.Name: SendingTime
Field.Description: Time of message transmission (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: Shares
Field.Description: Number of shares (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: Side
Field.Description: Side of order

Field.Name: Symbol
Field.Description: Ticker symbol

Field.Name: TargetCompID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify receiving firm.

Field.Name: TargetSubID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific individual or unit intended to receive message. "ADMIN" reserved for administrative messages not intended for a specific user.

Field.Name: Text
Field.Description: Free format text string (Note: this field does not have a specified maximum length)

Field.Name: TimeInForce
Field.Description: Specifies how long the order remains in effect. Absence of this field is interpreted as DAY.

Field.Name: TransactTime
Field.Description: Time of execution/order creation (expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: Urgency
Field.Description: Urgency flag

Field.Name: ValidUntilTime
Field.Description: Indicates expiration time of indication message (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: SettlmntTyp
Field.Description: Indicates order settlement period. Absence of this field is interpreted as Regular. Regular is defined as the default settlement period for the particular security on the exchange of execution.

Field.Name: FutSettDate
Field.Description: Specific date of trade settlement (SettlementDate) in YYYYMMDD format. Required when SettlmntTyp = 6 (Future) or SettlmntTyp = 8 (Sellers Option). (expressed in local time at place of settlement)

Field.Name: SymbolSfx
Field.Description: Additional information about the security (e.g. preferred, warrants, etc.). Note also see SecurityType. Valid values: As defined in the NYSE Stock and bond Symbol Directory and in the AMEX Fitch Directory

Field.Name: ListID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for list as assigned by institution, used to associate multiple individual orders. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which generate multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the ListID field to assure uniqueness across days.

Field.Name: ListSeqNo
Field.Description: Sequence of individual order within list (i.e. ListSeqNo of ListNoOrds, 2 of 25, 3 of 25, . . . )

Field.Name: TotNoOrders
Field.Description: Total number of list order entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoOrders in each message that has repeating list order entries related to the same ListID. Used to support fragmentation. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was named "ListNoOrds")

Field.Name: ListExecInst
Field.Description: Free format text message containing list handling and execution instructions.

Field.Name: AllocID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for allocation message. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: AllocTransType
Field.Description: Identifies allocation transaction type

Field.Name: RefAllocID
Field.Description: Reference identifier to be used with Replace, Cancel, and Calculated AllocTransType messages. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: NoOrders
Field.Description: Indicates number of orders to be combined for average pricing and allocation.

Field.Name: AvgPrxPrecision
Field.Description: Indicates number of decimal places to be used for average pricing. Absence of this field indicates that default precision arranged by the broker/institution is to be used.

Field.Name: TradeDate
Field.Description: Indicates date of trade referenced in this message in YYYYMMDD format. Absence of this field indicates current day (expressed in local time at place of trade).

Field.Name: ExecBroker
Field.Description: Identifies executing / give-up broker. Standard NASD market-maker mnemonic is preferred.

Field.Name: OpenClose
Field.Description: Indicates whether the resulting position after a trade should be an opening position or closing position. Used for omnibus accounting - where accounts are held on a gross basis instead of being netted together.

Field.Name: NoAllocs
Field.Description: Number of repeating AllocAccount/AllocPrice entries.

Field.Name: AllocAccount
Field.Description: Sub-account mnemonic

Field.Name: AllocShares
Field.Description: Number of shares to be allocated to specific sub-account (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: ProcessCode
Field.Description: Processing code for sub-account. Absence of this field in AllocAccount / AllocPrice/AllocShares / ProcessCode instance indicates regular trade.

Field.Name: NoRpts
Field.Description: Total number of reports within series.

Field.Name: RptSeq
Field.Description: Sequence number of message within report series.

Field.Name: CxlQty
Field.Description: Total number of shares canceled for this order. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: NoDlvyInst
Field.Description: Number of delivery instruction fields to follow No longer used. Included here for reference to prior versions.

Field.Name: DlvyInst
Field.Description: Free format text field to indicate delivery instructions No longer used. Included here for reference to prior versions.

Field.Name: AllocStatus
Field.Description: Identifies status of allocation.

Field.Name: AllocRejCode
Field.Description: Identifies reason for rejection.

Field.Name: Signature
Field.Description: Electronic signature

Field.Name: SecureDataLen
Field.Description: Length of encrypted message

Field.Name: SecureData
Field.Description: Actual encrypted data stream

Field.Name: BrokerOfCredit
Field.Description: Broker to receive trade credit.

Field.Name: SignatureLength
Field.Description: Number of bytes in signature field.

Field.Name: EmailType
Field.Description: Email message type.

Field.Name: RawDataLength
Field.Description: Number of bytes in raw data field.

Field.Name: RawData
Field.Description: Unformatted raw data, can include bitmaps, word processor documents, etc.

Field.Name: PossResend
Field.Description: Indicates that message may contain information that has been sent under another sequence number.

Field.Name: EncryptMethod
Field.Description: Method of encryption.

Field.Name: StopPx
Field.Description: Price per share

Field.Name: ExDestination
Field.Description: Execution destination as defined by institution when order is entered. Valid values: See Appendix C

Field.Name: CxlRejReason
Field.Description: Code to identify reason for cancel rejection.

Field.Name: OrdRejReason
Field.Description: Code to identify reason for order rejection.

Field.Name: IOIQualifier
Field.Description: Code to qualify IOI use.

Field.Name: WaveNo
Field.Description: Identifier to aid in the management of multiple lists derived from a single, master list.

Field.Name: Issuer
Field.Description: Company name of security issuer (e.g. International Business Machines)

Field.Name: SecurityDesc
Field.Description: Security description.

Field.Name: HeartBtInt
Field.Description: Heartbeat interval (seconds)

Field.Name: ClientID
Field.Description: Firm identifier used in third party-transactions (should not be a substitute for OnBehalfOfCompID/DeliverToCompID).

Field.Name: MinQty
Field.Description: Minimum quantity of an order to be executed. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: MaxFloor
Field.Description: Maximum number of shares within an order to be shown on the exchange floor at any given time. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: TestReqID
Field.Description: Identifier included in Test Request message to be returned in resulting Heartbeat

Field.Name: ReportToExch
Field.Description: Identifies party of trade responsible for exchange reporting.

Field.Name: LocateReqd
Field.Description: Indicates whether the broker is to locate the stock in conjunction with a short sell order.

Field.Name: OnBehalfOfCompID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify firm originating message if the message was delivered by a third party i.e. the third party firm identifier would be delivered in the SenderCompID field and the firm originating the message in this field.

Field.Name: OnBehalfOfSubID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (i.e. trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

Field.Name: QuoteID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for quote

Field.Name: NetMoney
Field.Description: Total amount due as the result of the transaction (e.g. for Buy order - principal + commission + fees) reported in currency of execution.

Field.Name: SettlCurrAmt
Field.Description: Total amount due expressed in settlement currency (includes the effect of the forex transaction)

Field.Name: SettlCurrency
Field.Description: Currency code of settlement denomination.

Field.Name: ForexReq
Field.Description: Indicates request for forex accommodation trade to be executed along with security transaction.

Field.Name: OrigSendingTime
Field.Description: Original time of message transmission (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT") when transmitting orders as the result of a resend request.

Field.Name: GapFillFlag
Field.Description: Indicates that the Sequence Reset message is replacing administrative or application messages which will not be resent.

Field.Name: NoExecs
Field.Description: No of execution repeating group entries to follow.

Field.Name: CxlType
Field.Description: No longer used. Included here for reference to prior versions.

Field.Name: ExpireTime
Field.Description: Time/Date of order expiration (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: DKReason
Field.Description: Reason for execution rejection.

Field.Name: DeliverToCompID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify the firm targeted to receive the message if the message is delivered by a third party i.e. the third party firm identifier would be delivered in the TargetCompID field and the ultimate receiver firm ID in this field.

Field.Name: DeliverToSubID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message recipient (i.e. trader) if the message is delivered by a third party

Field.Name: IOINaturalFlag
Field.Description: Indicates that IOI is the result of an existing agency order or a facilitation position resulting from an agency order, not from principal trading or order solicitation activity.

Field.Name: QuoteReqID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for quote request

Field.Name: BidPx
Field.Description: Bid price/rate

Field.Name: OfferPx
Field.Description: Offer price/rate

Field.Name: BidSize
Field.Description: Quantity of bid (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: OfferSize
Field.Description: Quantity of offer (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: NoMiscFees
Field.Description: Number of repeating groups of miscellaneous fees

Field.Name: MiscFeeAmt
Field.Description: Miscellaneous fee value

Field.Name: MiscFeeCurr
Field.Description: Currency of miscellaneous fee

Field.Name: MiscFeeType
Field.Description: Indicates type of miscellaneous fee.

Field.Name: PrevClosePx
Field.Description: Previous closing price of security.

Field.Name: ResetSeqNumFlag
Field.Description: Indicates that the both sides of the FIX session should reset sequence numbers.

Field.Name: SenderLocationID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator’s location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader)

Field.Name: TargetLocationID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message destination’s location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader)

Field.Name: OnBehalfOfLocationID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator’s location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

Field.Name: DeliverToLocationID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message recipient’s location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

Field.Name: NoRelatedSym
Field.Description: Specifies the number of repeating symbols specified.

Field.Name: Subject
Field.Description: The subject of an Email message

Field.Name: Headline
Field.Description: The headline of a News message

Field.Name: URLLink
Field.Description: A URL (Uniform Resource Locator) link to additional information (i.e. http://www.XYZ.com/research.html)

Field.Name: ExecType
Field.Description: Describes the specific ExecutionRpt (i.e. Pending Cancel) while OrdStatus will always identify the current order status (i.e. Partially Filled)

Field.Name: LeavesQty
Field.Description: Amount of shares open for further execution. If the OrdStatus is Canceled, DoneForTheDay, Expired, Calculated, or Rejected (in which case the order is no longer active) then LeavesQty could be 0, otherwise LeavesQty = OrderQty - CumQty. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: CashOrderQty
Field.Description: Specifies the approximate order quantity desired in total monetary units vs. as a number of shares. The broker would be responsible for converting and calculating a share quantity (OrderQty) based upon this amount to be used for the actual order and subsequent messages.

Field.Name: AllocAvgPx
Field.Description: AvgPx for a specific AllocAccount

Field.Name: AllocNetMoney
Field.Description: NetMoney for a specific AllocAccount

Field.Name: SettlCurrFxRate
Field.Description: Foreign exchange rate used to compute SettlCurrAmt from Currency to SettlCurrency

Field.Name: SettlCurrFxRateCalc
Field.Description: Specifies whether or not SettlCurrFxRate should be multiplied or divided.

Field.Name: NumDaysInterest
Field.Description: Number of Days of Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income

Field.Name: AccruedInterestRate
Field.Description: Accrued Interest Rate for convertible bonds and fixed income

Field.Name: AccruedInterestAmt
Field.Description: Amount of Accrued Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income

Field.Name: SettlInstMode
Field.Description: Indicates mode used for Settlement Instructions

Field.Name: AllocText
Field.Description: Free format text related to a specific AllocAccount.

Field.Name: SettlInstID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for Settlement Instructions message.

Field.Name: SettlInstTransType
Field.Description: Settlement Instructions message transaction type

Field.Name: EmailThreadID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for an email thread (new and chain of replies)

Field.Name: SettlInstSource
Field.Description: Indicates source of Settlement Instructions

Field.Name: SettlLocation
Field.Description: Identifies Settlement Depository or Country Code (ISITC spec)

Field.Name: SecurityType
Field.Description: Indicates type of security (ISITC spec)

Field.Name: EffectiveTime
Field.Description: Time the details within the message should take effect (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: StandInstDbType
Field.Description: Identifies the Standing Instruction database used

Field.Name: StandInstDbName
Field.Description: Name of the Standing Instruction database represented with StandInstDbType (i.e. the Global Custodian’s name).

Field.Name: StandInstDbID
Field.Description: Unique identifier used on the Standing Instructions database for the Standing Instructions to be referenced.

Field.Name: SettlDeliveryType
Field.Description: Identifies type of settlement

Field.Name: SettlDepositoryCode
Field.Description: Broker’s account code at the depository (i.e. CEDEL ID for CEDEL, FINS for DTC, or Euroclear ID for Euroclear) if SettlLocation is a depository

Field.Name: SettlBrkrCode
Field.Description: BIC (Bank Identification Code—Swift managed) code of the broker involved (i.e. for multi-company brokerage firms)

Field.Name: SettlInstCode
Field.Description: BIC (Bank Identification Code—Swift managed) code of the institution involved (i.e. for multi-company institution firms)

Field.Name: SecuritySettlAgentName
Field.Description: Name of SettlInstSource's local agent bank if SettlLocation is not a depository

Field.Name: SecuritySettlAgentCode
Field.Description: BIC (Bank Identification Code--Swift managed) code of the SettlInstSource's local agent bank if SettlLocation is not a depository

Field.Name: SecuritySettlAgentAcctNum
Field.Description: SettlInstSource's account number at local agent bank if SettlLocation is not a depository

Field.Name: SecuritySettlAgentAcctName
Field.Description: Name of SettlInstSource's account at local agent bank if SettlLocation is not a depository

Field.Name: SecuritySettlAgentContactName
Field.Description: Name of contact at local agent bank for SettlInstSource's account if SettlLocation is not a depository

Field.Name: SecuritySettlAgentContactPhone
Field.Description: Phone number for contact at local agent bank if SettlLocation is not a depository

Field.Name: CashSettlAgentName
Field.Description: Name of SettlInstSource's local agent bank if SettlDeliveryType=Free

Field.Name: CashSettlAgentCode
Field.Description: BIC (Bank Identification Code--Swift managed) code of the SettlInstSource's local agent bank if SettlDeliveryType=Free

Field.Name: CashSettlAgentAcctNum
Field.Description: SettlInstSource's account number at local agent bank if SettlDeliveryType=Free

Field.Name: CashSettlAgentAcctName
Field.Description: Name of SettlInstSource's account at local agent bank if SettlDeliveryType=Free

Field.Name: CashSettlAgentContactName
Field.Description: Name of contact at local agent bank for SettlInstSource's account if SettlDeliveryType=Free

Field.Name: CashSettlAgentContactPhone
Field.Description: Phone number for contact at local agent bank for SettlInstSource's account if SettlDeliveryType=Free

Field.Name: BidSpotRate
Field.Description: Bid F/X spot rate.y vary and not limited to four)

Field.Name: BidForwardPoints
Field.Description: Bid F/X forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

Field.Name: OfferSpotRate
Field.Description: Offer F/X spot rate.

Field.Name: OfferForwardPoints
Field.Description: Offer F/X forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

Field.Name: OrderQty2
Field.Description: OrderQty of the future part of a F/X swap order.

Field.Name: FutSettDate2
Field.Description: FutSettDate of the future part of a F/X swap order.

Field.Name: LastSpotRate
Field.Description: F/X spot rate.

Field.Name: LastForwardPoints
Field.Description: F/X forward points added to LastSpotRate. May be a negative value.

Field.Name: AllocLinkID
Field.Description: Can be used to link two different Allocation messages (each with unique AllocID) together, i.e. for F/X "Netting" or "Swaps". Should be unique.

Field.Name: AllocLinkType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of Allocation linkage when AllocLinkID is used.

Field.Name: SecondaryOrderID
Field.Description: Assigned by the party which accepts the order. Can be used to provide the OrderID used by an exchange or executing system.

Field.Name: NoIOIQualifiers
Field.Description: Number of repeating groups of IOIQualifiers.

Field.Name: MaturityMonthYear
Field.Description: Month and Year of the maturity for SecurityType=FUT or SecurityType=OPT. Required if MaturityDay is specified. Format: YYYYMM (i.e. 199903)

Field.Name: PutOrCall
Field.Description: Indicates whether an Option is for a put or call.

Field.Name: StrikePrice
Field.Description: Strike Price for an Option.

Field.Name: CoveredOrUncovered
Field.Description: Used for options

Field.Name: CustomerOrFirm
Field.Description: Used for options when delivering the order to an execution system/exchange to specify if the order is for a customer or the firm placing the order itself.

Field.Name: MaturityDay
Field.Description: Day of month used in conjunction with MaturityMonthYear to specify the maturity date for SecurityType=FUT or SecurityType=OPT.

Field.Name: OptAttribute
Field.Description: Can be used for SecurityType=OPT to identify a particular security.

Field.Name: SecurityExchange
Field.Description: Market used to help identify a security.

Field.Name: NotifyBrokerOfCredit
Field.Description: Indicates whether or not details should be communicated to BrokerOfCredit (i.e. step-in broker).

Field.Name: AllocHandlInst
Field.Description: Indicates how the receiver (i.e. third party) of Allocation message should handle/process the account details.

Field.Name: MaxShow
Field.Description: Maximum number of shares within an order to be shown to other customers (i.e. sent via an IOI). (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: PegDifference
Field.Description: Amount (signed) added to the price of the peg for a pegged order.

Field.Name: XmlDataLen
Field.Description: Length of the XmlData data block.

Field.Name: XmlData
Field.Description: Actual XML data stream (e.g. FIXML). See approriate XML reference (e.g. FIXML). Note: may contain embedded SOH characters.

Field.Name: SettlInstRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier for the SettlInstID with Cancel and Replace SettlInstTransType transaction types.

Field.Name: NoRoutingIDs
Field.Description: Number of repeating groups of RoutingID and RoutingType values. See Appendix L – Pre-Trade Message Targeting/Routing

Field.Name: RoutingType
Field.Description: Indicates the type of RoutingID specified.

Field.Name: RoutingID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify a specific routing destination.

Field.Name: SpreadToBenchmark
Field.Description: For Fixed Income. Basis points relative to a benchmark. To be expressed as "count of basis points" (vs. an absolute value). E.g. High Grade Corporate Bonds may express price as basis points relative to benchmark (the Benchmark field). Note: Basis points can be negative.

Field.Name: Benchmark
Field.Description: For Fixed Income. Identifies the benchmark (e.g. used in conjunction with the SpreadToBenchmark field).

Field.Name: CouponRate
Field.Description: For Fixed Income. Coupon rate of the bond. Will be zero for step-up bonds.

Field.Name: ContractMultiplier
Field.Description: Specifies the ratio or multiply factor to convert from contracts to shares (e.g. 1.0, 100, 1000, etc). Applicable For Fixed Income, Convertible Bonds, Derivatives, etc. Note: If used, quantities should be expressed in the "nominal" (e.g. contracts vs. shares) amount.

Field.Name: MDReqID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for Market Data Request

Field.Name: SubscriptionRequestType
Field.Description: Subscription Request Type

Field.Name: MarketDepth
Field.Description: Depth of market for Book Snapshot

Field.Name: MDUpdateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of Market Data update.

Field.Name: AggregatedBook
Field.Description: Specifies whether or not book entries should be aggregated.

Field.Name: NoMDEntryTypes
Field.Description: Number of MDEntryType fields requested.

Field.Name: NoMDEntries
Field.Description: Number of entries in Market Data message.

Field.Name: MDEntryType
Field.Description: Type Market Data entry.

Field.Name: MDEntryPx
Field.Description: Price of the Market Data Entry.

Field.Name: MDEntrySize
Field.Description: Number of shares represented by the Market Data Entry.

Field.Name: MDEntryDate
Field.Description: Date of Market Data Entry.

Field.Name: MDEntryTime
Field.Description: Time of Market Data Entry.

Field.Name: TickDirection
Field.Description: Direction of the "tick".

Field.Name: MDMkt
Field.Description: Market posting quote / trade. Valid values: See Appendix C

Field.Name: QuoteCondition
Field.Description: Space-delimited list of conditions describing a quote.

Field.Name: TradeCondition
Field.Description: Space-delimited list of conditions describing a trade

Field.Name: MDEntryID
Field.Description: Unique Market Data Entry identifier.

Field.Name: MDUpdateAction
Field.Description: Type of Market Data update action.

Field.Name: MDEntryRefID
Field.Description: Refers to a previous MDEntryID.

Field.Name: MDReqRejReason
Field.Description: Reason for the rejection of a Market Data request.

Field.Name: MDEntryOriginator
Field.Description: Originator of a Market Data Entry

Field.Name: LocationID
Field.Description: Identification of a Market Maker’s location

Field.Name: DeskID
Field.Description: Identification of a Market Maker’s desk

Field.Name: DeleteReason
Field.Description: Reason for deletion.

Field.Name: OpenCloseSettleFlag
Field.Description: Flag that identifies a price.

Field.Name: SellerDays
Field.Description: Specifies the number of days that may elapse before delivery of the security

Field.Name: MDEntryBuyer
Field.Description: Buying party in a trade

Field.Name: MDEntrySeller
Field.Description: Selling party in a trade

Field.Name: MDEntryPositionNo
Field.Description: Display position of a bid or offer, numbered from most competitive to least competitive, per market side, beginning with 1.

Field.Name: FinancialStatus
Field.Description: Identifies a firm’s financial status.

Field.Name: CorporateAction
Field.Description: Identifies the type of Corporate Action.

Field.Name: DefBidSize
Field.Description: Default Bid Size.

Field.Name: DefOfferSize
Field.Description: Default Offer Size.

Field.Name: NoQuoteEntries
Field.Description: The number of quote entries for a QuoteSet.

Field.Name: NoQuoteSets
Field.Description: The number of sets of quotes in the message.

Field.Name: QuoteAckStatus
Field.Description: Identifies the status of the quote acknowledgement.

Field.Name: QuoteCancelType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of quote cancel.

Field.Name: QuoteEntryID
Field.Description: Uniquely identifies the quote as part of a QuoteSet.

Field.Name: QuoteRejectReason
Field.Description: Reason Quote was rejected:

Field.Name: QuoteResponseLevel
Field.Description: Level of Response requested from receiver of quote messages.

Field.Name: QuoteSetID
Field.Description: Unique id for the Quote Set.

Field.Name: QuoteRequestType
Field.Description: Indicates the type of Quote Request being generated

Field.Name: TotQuoteEntries
Field.Description: Total number of quotes for the quote set across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoQuoteEntries in each message that has repeating quotes that are part of the same quote set.

Field.Name: UnderlyingIDSource
Field.Description: Underlying security’s IDSource.

Field.Name: UnderlyingIssuer
Field.Description: Underlying security’s Issuer. See Issuer field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecurityDesc
Field.Description: Underlying security’s SecurityDesc. See SecurityDesc field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecurityExchange
Field.Description: Underlying security’s SecurityExchange. Can be used to identify the underlying security.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecurityID
Field.Description: Underlying security’s SecurityID. See SecurityID field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecurityType
Field.Description: Underlying security’s SecurityType.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSymbol
Field.Description: Underlying security’s Symbol. See Symbol field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingSymbolSfx
Field.Description: Underlying security’s SymbolSfx. See SymbolSfx field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingMaturityMonthYear
Field.Description: Underlying security’s MaturityMonthYear. Required if UnderlyingMaturityDay is specified. See MaturityMonthYear field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingMaturityDay
Field.Description: Underlying security’s MaturityDay. See MaturityDay field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingPutOrCall
Field.Description: Underlying security’s PutOrCall. See PutOrCall field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingStrikePrice
Field.Description: Underlying security’s StrikePrice. See StrikePrice field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptAttribute
Field.Description: Underlying security’s OptAttribute. See OptAttribute field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingCurrency
Field.Description: Underlying security’s Currency. See Currency field for description and valid values

Field.Name: RatioQty
Field.Description: Quantity of a particular leg in the security.

Field.Name: SecurityReqID
Field.Description: Unique ID of a Security Definition Request.

Field.Name: SecurityRequestType
Field.Description: Type of Security Definition Request.

Field.Name: SecurityResponseID
Field.Description: Unique ID of a Security Definition message.

Field.Name: SecurityResponseType
Field.Description: Type of Security Definition message response.

Field.Name: SecurityStatusReqID
Field.Description: Unique ID of a Security Status Request message.

Field.Name: UnsolicitedIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether or not message is being sent as a result of a subscription request or not.

Field.Name: SecurityTradingStatus
Field.Description: Identifies the trading status applicable to the transaction.

Field.Name: HaltReason
Field.Description: Denotes the reason for the Opening Delay or Trading Halt.

Field.Name: InViewOfCommon
Field.Description: Indicates whether or not the halt was due to Common Stock trading being halted.

Field.Name: DueToRelated
Field.Description: Indicates whether or not the halt was due to the Related Security being halted.

Field.Name: BuyVolume
Field.Description: Number of shares bought.

Field.Name: SellVolume
Field.Description: Number of shares sold.

Field.Name: HighPx
Field.Description: Represents an indication of the high end of the price range for a security prior to the open or reopen

Field.Name: LowPx
Field.Description: Represents an indication of the low end of the price range for a security prior to the open or reopen

Field.Name: Adjustment
Field.Description: Identifies the type of adjustment.

Field.Name: TradSesReqID
Field.Description: Unique ID of a Trading Session Status message.

Field.Name: TradingSessionID
Field.Description: Identifier for Trading Session Can be used to represent a specific market trading session (e.g. "PRE-OPEN", "CROSS_2", "AFTER-HOURS", "TOSTNET1", "TOSTNET2", etc). Values should be bi-laterally agreed to between counterparties.

Field.Name: ContraTrader
Field.Description: Identifies the trader (e.g. "badge number") of the ContraBroker.

Field.Name: TradSesMethod
Field.Description: Method of trading

Field.Name: TradSesMode
Field.Description: Trading Session Mode

Field.Name: TradSesStatus
Field.Description: State of the trading session.

Field.Name: TradSesStartTime
Field.Description: Starting time of the trading session

Field.Name: TradSesOpenTime
Field.Description: Time of the opening of the trading session

Field.Name: TradSesPreCloseTime
Field.Description: Time of the pre-closed of the trading session

Field.Name: TradSesCloseTime
Field.Description: Closing time of the trading session

Field.Name: TradSesEndTime
Field.Description: End time of the trading session

Field.Name: NumberOfOrders
Field.Description: Number of orders in the market.

Field.Name: MessageEncoding
Field.Description: Type of message encoding (non-ASCII (non-English) characters) used in a message’s "Encoded" fields.

Field.Name: EncodedIssuerLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedIssuer field.

Field.Name: EncodedIssuer
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Issuer field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Issuer field.

Field.Name: EncodedSecurityDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedSecurityDesc field.

Field.Name: EncodedSecurityDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the SecurityDesc field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the SecurityDesc field.

Field.Name: EncodedListExecInstLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedListExecInst field.

Field.Name: EncodedListExecInst
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the ListExecInst field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the ListExecInst field.

Field.Name: EncodedTextLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedText field.

Field.Name: EncodedText
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Text field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Text field.

Field.Name: EncodedSubjectLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedSubject field.

Field.Name: EncodedSubject
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Subject field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Subject field.

Field.Name: EncodedHeadlineLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedHeadline field.

Field.Name: EncodedHeadline
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Headline field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Headline field.

Field.Name: EncodedAllocTextLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedAllocText field.

Field.Name: EncodedAllocText
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the AllocText field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the AllocText field.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingIssuerLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingIssuer field.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingIssuer
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingIssuer field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingIssuer field.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDesc field.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingSecurityDesc field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingSecurityeDesc field.

Field.Name: AllocPrice
Field.Description: Executed price for an AllocAccount entry used when using "executed price" vs. "average price" allocations (e.g. Japan).

Field.Name: QuoteSetValidUntilTime
Field.Description: Indicates expiration time of this particular QuoteSet (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: QuoteEntryRejectReason
Field.Description: Reason Quote Entry was rejected:

Field.Name: LastMsgSeqNumProcessed
Field.Description: The last MsgSeqNum value received and processed. Can be specified on every message sent. Useful for detecting a backlog with a counterparty.

Field.Name: OnBehalfOfSendingTime
Field.Description: Used when a message is sent via a "hub" or "service bureau". If A sends to Q (the hub) who then sends to B via a separate FIX session, then when Q sends to B the value of this field should represent the SendingTime on the message A sent to Q. (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: RefTagID
Field.Description: The tag number of the FIX field being referenced.

Field.Name: RefMsgType
Field.Description: The MsgType of the FIX message being referenced.

Field.Name: SessionRejectReason
Field.Description: Code to identify reason for a session-level Reject message.

Field.Name: BidRequestTransType
Field.Description: Identifies the Bid Request message type.

Field.Name: ContraBroker
Field.Description: Identifies contra broker. Standard NASD market-maker mnemonic is preferred.

Field.Name: ComplianceID
Field.Description: ID used to represent this transaction for compliance purposes (e.g. OATS reporting).

Field.Name: SolicitedFlag
Field.Description: Indicates whether or not the order was solicited.

Field.Name: ExecRestatementReason
Field.Description: Code to identify reason for an ExecutionRpt message sent with ExecType=Restated or used when communicating an unsolicited cancel.

Field.Name: BusinessRejectRefID
Field.Description: The value of the business-level "ID" field on the message being referenced.

Field.Name: BusinessRejectReason
Field.Description: Code to identify reason for a Business Message Reject message.

Field.Name: GrossTradeAmt
Field.Description: Total amount traded (e.g. CumQty * AvgPx) expressed in units of currency.

Field.Name: NoContraBrokers
Field.Description: The number of ContraBroker entries.

Field.Name: MaxMessageSize
Field.Description: Maximum number of bytes supported for a single message.

Field.Name: NoMsgTypes
Field.Description: Number of MsgTypes in repeating group.

Field.Name: MsgDirection
Field.Description: Specifies the direction of the messsage.

Field.Name: NoTradingSessions
Field.Description: Number of TradingSessionIDs in repeating group.

Field.Name: TotalVolumeTraded
Field.Description: Total volume (quantity) traded.

Field.Name: DiscretionInst
Field.Description: Code to identify the price a DiscretionOffset is related to and should be mathematically added to.

Field.Name: DiscretionOffset
Field.Description: Amount (signed) added to the "related to" price specified via DiscretionInst.

Field.Name: BidID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for Bid Response as assigned by broker. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day.

Field.Name: ClientBidID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for a Bid Request as assigned by institution. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day.

Field.Name: ListName
Field.Description: Descriptive name for list order.

Field.Name: TotalNumSecurities
Field.Description: Total number of securities.

Field.Name: BidType
Field.Description: Code to identify the type of Bid Request.

Field.Name: NumTickets
Field.Description: Total number of tickets.

Field.Name: SideValue1
Field.Description: Amounts in currency

Field.Name: SideValue2
Field.Description: Amounts in currency

Field.Name: NoBidDescriptors
Field.Description: Number of BidDescriptor entries.

Field.Name: BidDescriptorType
Field.Description: Code to identify the type of BidDescriptor.

Field.Name: BidDescriptor
Field.Description: BidDescriptor value. Usage depends upon BidDescriptorType.

Field.Name: SideValueInd
Field.Description: Code to identify which "SideValue" the value refers to. SideValue1 and SideValue2 are used as opposed to Buy or Sell so that the basket can be quoted either way as Buy or Sell.

Field.Name: LiquidityPctLow
Field.Description: Liquidity indicator or lower limit if TotalNumSecurities > 1. Represented as a percentage.

Field.Name: LiquidityPctHigh
Field.Description: Upper liquidity indicator if TotalNumSecurities > 1. Represented as a percentage.

Field.Name: LiquidityValue
Field.Description: Value between LiquidityPctLow and LiquidityPctHigh in Currency

Field.Name: EFPTrackingError
Field.Description: Eg Used in EFP trades 12% (EFP – Exchange for Physical ). Represented as a percentage.

Field.Name: FairValue
Field.Description: Used in EFP trades

Field.Name: OutsideIndexPct
Field.Description: Used in EFP trades. Represented as a percentage.

Field.Name: ValueOfFutures
Field.Description: Used in EFP trades

Field.Name: LiquidityIndType
Field.Description: Code to identify the type of liquidity indicator.

Field.Name: WtAverageLiquidity
Field.Description: Overall weighted average liquidity expressed as a % of average daily volume. Represented as a percentage.

Field.Name: ExchangeForPhysical
Field.Description: Indicates whether or not to exchange for phsyical.

Field.Name: OutMainCntryUIndex
Field.Description: Value of stocks in Currency

Field.Name: CrossPercent
Field.Description: Percentage of program that crosses in Currency. Represented as a percentage.

Field.Name: ProgRptReqs
Field.Description: Code to identify the desired frequency of progress reports.

Field.Name: ProgPeriodInterval
Field.Description: Time in minutes between each ListStatus report sent by SellSide. Zero means don’t send status.

Field.Name: IncTaxInd
Field.Description: Code to represent whether value is net (inclusive of tax) or gross.

Field.Name: NumBidders
Field.Description: Indicates the total number of bidders on the list

Field.Name: TradeType
Field.Description: Code to represent the type of trade.

Field.Name: BasisPxType
Field.Description: Code to represent the basis price type.

Field.Name: NoBidComponents
Field.Description: Indicates the number of list entries.

Field.Name: Country
Field.Description: ISO Country Code in field

Field.Name: TotNoStrikes
Field.Description: Total number of strike price entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoStrikes in each message that has repeating strike price entries related to the same ListID. Used to support fragmentation.

Field.Name: PriceType
Field.Description: Code to represent the price type.

Field.Name: DayOrderQty
Field.Description: For GT orders, the OrderQty less all shares (adjusted for stock splits) that traded on previous days. DayOrderQty = OrderQty – (CumQty - DayCumQty)

Field.Name: DayCumQty
Field.Description: The number of shares on a GT order that have traded today.

Field.Name: DayAvgPx
Field.Description: The average price of shares on a GT order that have traded today.

Field.Name: GTBookingInst
Field.Description: Code to identify whether to book out executions on a part-filled GT order on the day of execution or to accumulate.

Field.Name: NoStrikes
Field.Description: Number of list strike price entries.

Field.Name: ListStatusType
Field.Description: Code to represent the price type.

Field.Name: NetGrossInd
Field.Description: Code to represent whether value is net (inclusive of tax) or gross.

Field.Name: ListOrderStatus
Field.Description: Code to represent the status of a list order.

Field.Name: ExpireDate
Field.Description: Date of order expiration (last day the order can trade), always expressed in terms of the local market date. The time at which the order expires is determined by the local market’s business practices

Field.Name: ListExecInstType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of ListExecInst.

Field.Name: CxlRejResponseTo
Field.Description: Identifies the type of request that a Cancel Reject is in response to.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCouponRate
Field.Description: Underlying security’s CouponRate. See CouponRate field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingContractMultiplier
Field.Description: Underlying security’s ContractMultiplier. See ContractMultiplier field for description

Field.Name: ContraTradeQty
Field.Description: Quantity traded with the ContraBroker.

Field.Name: ContraTradeTime
Field.Description: Identifes the time of the trade with the ContraBroker. (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: ClearingFirm
Field.Description: Firm that will clear the trade. Used if different from the executing firm.

Field.Name: ClearingAccount
Field.Description: Supplemental accounting information forwared to clearing house/firm.

Field.Name: LiquidityNumSecurities
Field.Description: Number of Securites between LiquidityPctLow and LiquidityPctHigh in Currency.

Field.Name: MultiLegReportingType
Field.Description: Used to indicate what an Execution Report represents (e.g. used with multi-leg securiteis, such as option strategies, spreads, etc.).

Field.Name: StrikeTime
Field.Description: The time at which current market prices are used to determine the value of a basket.

Field.Name: ListStatusText
Field.Description: Free format text string related to List Status.

Field.Name: EncodedListStatusTextLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedListStatusText field.

Field.Name: EncodedListStatusText
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the ListStatusText field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the ListStatusText field.
